{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Shopify Theme from Scratch Part 9: search.liquid","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>\t\t\t\t<div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:23.25%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/19bd1/part9_banner.png 163w,\n/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/d3bcb/part9_banner.png 325w,\n/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/dbb61/part9_banner.png 650w,\n/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/8ff1e/part9_banner.png 800w\" src=\"/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/dbb61/part9_banner.png\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/19bd1/part9_banner.png 163w,\n/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/d3bcb/part9_banner.png 325w,\n/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/dbb61/part9_banner.png 650w,\n/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/8ff1e/part9_banner.png 800w\" src=\"/static/a7fc8702afe9d286e7f99a775638c962/dbb61/part9_banner.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></p>\n<p>In Part 9 of the Shopify Theme from Scratch series, we&#x2019;re going to be the search.liquid template, where customers can search through a shop for products, pages, and blog articles.</p>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s gitter done! Head on over to &#x201C;yourshop.myshopify.com/search&#x201D; to see your search page.</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">1. Add the search form</h2>\n<p>The first thing we&#x2019;re going to do is add the search form. Open search.liquid, and replace its contents with the following code:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<h2>Search</h2>\n<div class=\"search-form\">\n<form action=\"/search\" method=\"get\" class=\"search-form\" role=\"search\">\n  \n    <input type=\"text\" name=\"q\" value=\"{{ search.terms | escape }}\">\n    <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Search store\" class=\"btn\">\n  \n</form>\n</div>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>You will now see a snazzy search form (Figure 9.1).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/search-page.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:46.31685166498486%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/aca85/search-page.jpg 163w,\n/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/0954f/search-page.jpg 325w,\n/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/a111b/search-page.jpg 650w,\n/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/ce471/search-page.jpg 975w,\n/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/a9e20/search-page.jpg 991w\" src=\"/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/a111b/search-page.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/aca85/search-page.jpg 163w,\n/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/0954f/search-page.jpg 325w,\n/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/a111b/search-page.jpg 650w,\n/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/ce471/search-page.jpg 975w,\n/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/a9e20/search-page.jpg 991w\" src=\"/static/63372beeb6fa65cf239d8d6fba563f9d/a111b/search-page.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 9.1: search bar on search.liquid</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">2. Check to see if a search was performed</h2>\n<p>Before we output the contents of the search result, we need to add an if-statement to see if a search query was actually submitted or not. This is done to prevent the search page from searching for a blank string when you visit it.</p>\n<p>Enter the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<h2>Search</h2>\n<div class=\"search-form\">\n<form action=\"/search\" method=\"get\" class=\"search-form\" role=\"search\">\n  \n    <input type=\"text\" name=\"q\" value=\"{{ search.terms | escape }}\">\n    <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Search store\" class=\"btn\">\n  \n</form>\n</div>\n\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% if search.performed %}\n{% endif %}</span>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<h2 class=\"step\">3. Add a for-loop to output the search results</h2>\n<p>Now let&#x2019;s add a for-loop to output the search results. We want to look through the &#x2018;results&#x2019; array that is part of the search object to see if there is anything to output. For more on the search object, please see the <a href=\"http://docs.shopify.com/themes/liquid-variables/search\">docs page</a>.</p>\n<p>Within the if-statement that we just added, put in the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n{% if search.performed %}    \n    <span style=\"color:red;\">{% if search.results_count == 0 %}  \n      Your search for &quot;{{ search.terms }}&quot; did not yield any results.<p></p>              \n    {% else %}  \n      {% for item in search.results %}      \n        <div class=\"search-result clearfix\">\n          <h3>{{ item.title | link_to: item.url }}</h3>\n          {% if item.featured_image %}\n          <div class=\"product-thumb left\">\n            <a href=\"{{ item.url }}\" title=\"{{ item.title | escape }}\">\n              {{ item.featured_image.src | product_img_url: &apos;small&apos; | img_tag: item.featured_image.alt }}\n            </a>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"search-text left\">{{ item.content | strip_html | truncatewords: 40 | highlight: search.terms }}</div>\n          {% else %}\n          <div>{{ item.content | strip_html | truncatewords: 40 | highlight: search.terms }}</div>\n          {% endif %}\n        </div>\n        {% endfor %}\n    {% endif %}</span>\n{% endif %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Now, using the search form that we added in Step 1, try searching for &#x201C;lorem&#x201D; (it should be part of the descriptions of the products we uploaded in The Setup). You should now see the results of the search result being listed:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/search-results.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:85.69989929506546%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/aca85/search-results.jpg 163w,\n/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/0954f/search-results.jpg 325w,\n/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/a111b/search-results.jpg 650w,\n/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/ce471/search-results.jpg 975w,\n/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/014e1/search-results.jpg 993w\" src=\"/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/a111b/search-results.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/aca85/search-results.jpg 163w,\n/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/0954f/search-results.jpg 325w,\n/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/a111b/search-results.jpg 650w,\n/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/ce471/search-results.jpg 975w,\n/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/014e1/search-results.jpg 993w\" src=\"/static/7aa5dd59253f839aed5eb54d42e43c64/a111b/search-results.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 9.2: Search results being listed (we&#x2019;ll pretty it up in step 5)</div>\n<h3>What is {% if item.featured_image %} there for?</h3>\n<p>In the for-loop to output the search results, you may have noticed an odd-looking if-statement. This if-statement checks to see if the search result contains a featured_image, or in other words, it <em>checks to see if the result is a product</em>. If the search result is a product, we want to output its corresponding image. If the search is <strong>not</strong> a product, we&#x2019;ll just output the text of the page/blog article.</p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">4. Paginate the search results</h2>\n<p>Like we did on collection.liquid and blog.liquid, we&#x2019;re going to paginate the number of search results that can be shown per page on search.liquid. At the very top of search.liquid, add the following line of code in red:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% paginate search.results by 5 %}</span>\n\n<h2>Search</h2>\n</code><div class=\"search-form\"><code markup=\"span\">\n</code><form action=\"/search\" method=\"get\" class=\"search-form\" role=\"search\"><code markup=\"span\">\n  \n    <input type=\"text\" name=\"q\" value=\"{{ search.terms | escape }}\">\n    <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Search store\" class=\"btn\">\n...\n</code>\n\n<p>&#x2026;and at the very bottom of search.liquid, add the following:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n{% if paginate.pages &gt; 1 %}\n<div class=\"pagination\">\n  {{ paginate | default_pagination }}\n</div>\n{% endif %}\n\n{% endpaginate %}    \n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>If you have more than 5 search results, you should now see the page being paginated (Figure 9.3). Feel free to change the &#x2018;paginate by&#x2019; value to something else!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/search-pagination.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:39.54410307234886%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/aca85/search-pagination.jpg 163w,\n/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/0954f/search-pagination.jpg 325w,\n/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/a111b/search-pagination.jpg 650w,\n/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/ce471/search-pagination.jpg 975w,\n/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/0110e/search-pagination.jpg 1009w\" src=\"/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/a111b/search-pagination.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/aca85/search-pagination.jpg 163w,\n/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/0954f/search-pagination.jpg 325w,\n/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/a111b/search-pagination.jpg 650w,\n/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/ce471/search-pagination.jpg 975w,\n/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/0110e/search-pagination.jpg 1009w\" src=\"/static/d58edde1258c6588401eee1fbbad18c6/a111b/search-pagination.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 9.3: pagination on the search page</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">5. Add the CSS for the search page</h2>\n<p>Now let&#x2019;s pretty up the search results a bit. Open the style.css file, and insert the following code at the very bottom of the file.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n/**** search.liquid ****/\n\n.search-form input[type=&apos;text&apos;]{border:1px solid #ccc; padding:6px;}\n.search-result{margin-bottom:20px;}\n.search-text{width:818px; padding-left:20px;}\n.highlight{color:#ff0000;}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Your search results will now be laid out much nicer.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/search-page-styled.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:65%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/aca85/search-page-styled.jpg 163w,\n/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/0954f/search-page-styled.jpg 325w,\n/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/a111b/search-page-styled.jpg 650w,\n/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/ce471/search-page-styled.jpg 975w,\n/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/96f4b/search-page-styled.jpg 980w\" src=\"/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/a111b/search-page-styled.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/aca85/search-page-styled.jpg 163w,\n/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/0954f/search-page-styled.jpg 325w,\n/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/a111b/search-page-styled.jpg 650w,\n/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/ce471/search-page-styled.jpg 975w,\n/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/96f4b/search-page-styled.jpg 980w\" src=\"/static/530ad5dbd39ee2505d6072e448bc2e5d/a111b/search-page-styled.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 9.4: Pretty search results!</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">6. Add a search bar to the header toolbar</h2>\n<p>The last thing we&#x2019;re going to do is add a search bar inside the black tool bar that sits on top of the shop. To do this, we need to go back to theme.liquid (remember &#x2013; as a rule of thumb, elements of a theme that are on every page of the shop are typically found in theme.liquid).</p>\n<p>Open theme.liquid, and insert the code in red to the location specified below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<div class=\"header-toolbar\">\n    <div class=\"container clearfix\">\n          <span style=\"color:red;\"><div class=\"header-search right\">\n             \n                <input name=\"q\" type=\"text\" class=\"search-field\" placeholder=\"Search store...\">\n                <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn \" value=\"Search\">\n                        \n          </div></span>      \n          <div class=\"cart-info right\">\n            Cart: <a href=\"/cart\">{{ cart.item_count }} {{ cart.item_count | pluralize: &apos;item&apos;, &apos;items&apos; }} ({{ cart.total_price | money }})</a>\n          </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</code>\n</pre></form>\n<p>You&#x2019;ll now have a handy little search bar at the top of the theme that you can use anywhere in the shop (Figure 9.5)! &#x1F600;</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/search-bar.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:27.43718592964824%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/aca85/search-bar.jpg 163w,\n/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/0954f/search-bar.jpg 325w,\n/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/a111b/search-bar.jpg 650w,\n/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/ce471/search-bar.jpg 975w,\n/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/3ebf2/search-bar.jpg 995w\" src=\"/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/a111b/search-bar.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/aca85/search-bar.jpg 163w,\n/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/0954f/search-bar.jpg 325w,\n/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/a111b/search-bar.jpg 650w,\n/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/ce471/search-bar.jpg 975w,\n/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/3ebf2/search-bar.jpg 995w\" src=\"/static/732fd360ce768029852d0ca20f80601c/a111b/search-bar.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 9.5: search bar inside the toolbar</div>\n<p>That&#x2019;s it for this week!</p>\n<p><a href=\"/shopify-theme-from-scratch/\">&#x2190; Back to table of contents</a>\t\t</p>\n</div></pre></body></html>","wordpress_id":3475},"allWordpressWpComments":{"edges":[{"node":{"content":"<p>Hi tetchi,</p>\n<p>Thank you for this blog &#8211; super helpful!  I was wondering if there was a way to order search results by collection so that search will display results for one collection (or product type or vendor) followed by another?  For example &#8211; I want to add a sold collection, but want the sold products to appear under available products in my search results.</p>\n<p>Thanks tetchi!</p>\n","author_name":"Michael Nathan","date":"June 17th, 2014"}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-9","wordpressId":3475,"newerPostSlug":"no-tutorial-this-week","olderPostSlug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-8"}}